04/03/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The trial of ultranationalist group leader Obraz Mladen Obradovic opened on Thursday (March 3rd) in Belgrade. He is charged with orchestrating protests during Belgrade's Gay Pride Parade in October. Obradovic denies any responsibility for the clashes with police and blamed the authorities for trying to discredit his movement. More than 140 police officers were injured during clashes with demonstrators. Nearly 250 people were detained during and after the violence, which caused significant property damage. (RTS, Tanjug, Beta - 03/03/11)
